{"name":"Chainaxe","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p><span dir=\"ltr\" style=\"left: 95.0416px; top: 742.782px; font-size: 12px; font-family: sans-serif; transform: scaleX(0.734273);\">Weapon is Two-Handed</span></p>\n<p>While the chainsword can be wielded with finesse, the chainaxe is a more simple and savage affair. The added leverage of the long haft allows its wide chain edge makes for a heavier strike with each blow, but with less control or precision. Most wield the chainaxe for just these reasons, and savour the terror and destruction they cause. This is a twohanded melee weapon.</p>","availability":"scarce","weight":13,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"rending","penetration":"2","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Tearing","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Meele/chainaxe.svg","effects":[],"_id":"2GXxMDrAdZXd2Vd3"}
{"name":"Eviscerator","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p><span dir=\"ltr\" style=\"left: 95.0416px; top: 742.782px; font-size: 12px; font-family: sans-serif; transform: scaleX(0.734273);\">Weapon is Two-Handed</span></p>\n<p>One of the largest chain weapons, the eviscerator is a huge chainsword, often double-edged, that requires both hands to use. The priests of the Adeptus Ministorum often wield them with unrestrained fury against heretics, caring little if they themselves are injured in each wild swing. If an attack made with an eviscerator triggers Righteous Fury (see page 227), the wielder adds +1 to the resulting roll on the appropriate Rending Critical Effects Table. This is a two-handed melee weapon.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":15,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"2d10","damageType":"rending","penetration":"9","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Razor Sharp, Tearing, Unwieldy","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Meele/eviscerator.svg","effects":[],"_id":"LfaVxI3I4ZzOsSvT"}
{"name":"Chainsword","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>The most common type of chain weapon, these heavy swords usually only have the tip and one edge exposed for the spinning, deadly chain teeth. Despite their barbarous nature, many elaborate fencing schools devoted to the artistic practice of the chainsword exist across the Imperium. For many users, however, any strike is enough to deal with most enemies, leaving behind only torn flesh and blood.</p>","availability":"average","weight":6,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+2","damageType":"rending","penetration":"2","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Balanced, Tearing","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Meele/chainsword.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Noi7aUQD3f1sMbXc"}
{"name":"Chainblade","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Chainblades are one of the smallest chain weapons, little more than a knife with a tiny chain around its edge. The size is deceptive, for the extra tearing the chain provides makes it much more effective than any ordinary dagger.</p>","availability":"scarce","weight":2,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+1","damageType":"rending","penetration":"1","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Tearing","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Meele/chainknife.svg","effects":[],"_id":"uqJyeCo5Eh7IecdM"}
